This case has not been concluded. Unless a judgment of conviction is entered, the defendant is presumed innocent of all charges.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Gregory Michael Neuenfeldt appeared by video, in custody in HOC.  Attorney Alexander J. Kostal appeared by video for Gregory Michael Neuenfeldt.  Prosecuting attorney Navjot Singh Hira in court in person for the State of Wisconsin. 

Case set for a Preliminary Hearing. Parties are advised that this case is assigned to Branch 12, Judge David Borowski. Defendant waived Preliminary Hearing. Preliminary Hearing Questionnaire and Waiver received and filed. Probable cause has been found and the defendant is bound over for trial.  Original Information e-filed, copy given to defense counsel who waived reading. Defense enters a plea of not guilty on behalf of the defendant. Case is adjourned to Br. 12.
Scheduling conference scheduled for November 16, 2022 at 10:30 am.

Defendant Gregory Michael Neuenfeldt appeared by video, in custody in HOC.  Attorney Alexander J. Kostal appeared by video for Gregory Michael Neuenfeldt.  Prosecuting attorney Nate Kristian McClure in court in person for the State of Wisconsin. 

Case is set for a Preliminary Hearing. State's Witness was present. Defense Counsel informs the court that the defendant would like to waive the Preliminary Hearing but he does not have access to the waiver form. Case is adjourned. Court orders case adjourned for CAUSE for a Status Conference. Defense Counsel motions to be heard on bail. Court grants the motion. Bail not amended. Court orders the bail to remain the same.
Status Conference scheduled for October 20, 2022 at 01:30 pm.
